<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="108" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,770,796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="108">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the lax, many-flowered panicle-like inflorescence, which is unique within the family of 
<taxonomicName box="[365,507,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="108" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="family">Annonaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,991,842,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="108" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,868]" box="[189,991,842,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,842,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="108">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<collectingCountry box="[370,449,842,868]" name="Gabon" pageId="2" pageNumber="108">Gabon</collectingCountry>
, provinces 
<collectingRegion box="[576,668,842,868]" country="Gabon" name="Estuaire" pageId="2" pageNumber="108">Estuaire</collectingRegion>
and 
